Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Lightly grease a large baking dish. Season the chicken with salt, pepper, and cinnamon. Arrange in the prepared baking dish. In a bowl, mix the molasses, vinegar, and mustard. Bake chicken 20 minutes in the preheated oven. Coat chicken with the molasses mixture. Continue baking 20 minutes, or until chicken juices run clear.